t with [[Israel]]i prime minister [[Benjamin Netanyahu]].\n|April 29, 2018\n|-\n|{{flag|Jordan}}\n|[[Amman]]\n|Met with [[Abdullah II of Jordan|King Abdullah II]] and Foreign Minister [[Ayman Safadi]].  Also met with Japanese foreign minister [[Taro Kono]].<ref name=\"Pompeo\">{{cite web|title=Travel to Belgium, Saudi Arabia, Israel, Jordan, April 26-30, 2018|url=https://www.state.gov/secretary/travel/2018/t6/index.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180428093305/https://www.state.gov/secretary/travel/2018/t6/index.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=28 April 2018|publisher=US State Department|accessdate=21 October 2018|language=en}} {{PD-notice}}</ref>\n|April 30, 2018\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" |2\n|{{flag|North Korea}}\n|[[Pyongyang]]\n|Met with Chairman [[Kim Jong-un]] and other North Korean government officials. Also secured the release of three Americans.<ref name=\"Pompeo2\">{{cite web|title=Travel to Japan and North Korea, May 8-9, 2018\n|url=https://www.state.gov/secretary/travel/2018/t7/index.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180509042044/https://www.state.gov/secretary/travel/2018/t7/index.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=9 May 2018|publisher=US State Department|accessdate=21 October 2018|language=en}} {{PD-notice}}</ref>\n|May 8\u20139, 2018\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" |3\n|{{flag|Canada}}\n|[[La Malbaie]]\n|Accompanied President [[Donald Trump|Trump]] to the [[44th G7 summit|G-7 meetings]].\n|June 9, 2018\n|-\n|{{flag|Singapore}}\n|[[Singapore]]\n|Participated in the president's [[2018 North Korea\u2013United States Singapore Summit|summit]] with North Korean leader [[Kim Jong-un]] and bilateral events with Singaporean prime minister [[Lee Hsien Loong]].\n|June 10\u201313, 2018\n|-\n|{{flag|South Korea}}\n|[[Seoul]]\n|Met with senior Korean and Japanese officials to discuss the U.S.\u2013Republic of Korea alliance, the U.S.\u2013Japan alliance, and next steps in a shared approach to North Korea.\n|June 13\u201314, 2018\n|-\n|{{flag|China}}\n|[[Beijing]]\n|Met with Chinese officials on bilateral, regional, and global issues that affect both countries.<ref name=\"Pompeo3\">{{cite web|title=Travel to Canada, Singapore, South Korea, and China, June 9-14, 2018\n|url=https://www.state.gov/secretary/travel/2018/t9/index.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180609230703/https://www.state.gov/secretary/travel/2018/t9/index.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=9 June 2018|publisher=US State Department|accessdate=21 October 2018|language=en}} {{PD-notice}}</ref>\n|June 14, 2018\n|-\n| rowspan=\"6\" |4\n|{{flag|North Korea}}\n|[[Pyongyang]]\n|Continued consultations and implementation of the forward progress made by President Trump and Chairman Kim in Singapore.\n|July 5\u20137, 2018\n|-\n|{{flag|Japan}}\n|[[Tokyo]]\n|Met with Japanese and South Korean leaders to discuss our shared commitment to the final, fully verified denuclearization of the DPRK, as well as other bilateral and regional issues.\n|July 7\u20138, 2018\n|-\n|{{flag|Vietnam}}\n|[[Hanoi]]\n|Met with senior Vietnamese officials to discuss our shared commitment to the final, fully verified denuclearization of the DPRK and other bilateral and regional issues.\n|July 8\u20139, 2018\n|-\n|{{flag|Afghanistan}}\n|[[Kabul]]\n|Met with Afghan officials.\n|July 9, 2018\n|-\n|{{flag|United Arab Emirates}}\n|[[Abu Dhabi]]\n|Met with UAE leaders to discuss ways to further strengthen the U.S.\u2013UAE partnership.\n|July 9\u201310, 2018\n|-\n|{{flag|Belgium}}\n|[[Brussels]]\n|Accompanied President [[Donald Trump|Trump]] to the [[2018 Brussels summit|NATO Summit]] and also participated in the U.S.\u2013EU Energy Council and co-hosted a meeting of foreign ministers of the Global Coalition to Defeat ISIS.<ref name=\"Pompeo4\">{{cite web|title=Travel to Pyongyang, Tokyo, Hanoi, Kabul, Abu Dhabi, and Brussels, July 5-12, 2018\n|url=https://www.state.gov/secretary/travel/2018/t10/index.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709054926/https://www.state.gov/secr